<%- include('/partials/header', {
  domain: 'Components',
  id: 'badges',
  page: 'Badges',
  noContentPadding: true,
}) %>

<div class="row">
  <div class="col-12 background-light-grey pt-3">
    <ul class="raul-nav nav nav-tabs raul-nav-underline" role="tablist">
      <li class="nav-item">
        <a
          class="nav-link active"
          href="#html-version"
          role="tab"
          data-toggle="tab"
          aria-expanded="true"
        >
          HTML version
        </a>
      </li>
    </ul>
  </div>
</div>

<div class="raul-tab-content tab-content mt-3">
  <div role="tabpanel" class="tab-pane active" id="html-version">
    <h2>Styled Bootstrap badges</h2>

    <p>
      The following is the preferred way of adding markup for badges. Under the hood it is
      just reusing available bootstrap badges with custom styling. This will be especially
      helpful to teams that are already using bootstrap as part of their system.
    </p>

    <div class="raul-card">
      <span class="badge badge-primary">33</span>
      <span class="badge badge-primary">
        <i class="fa fa-dribbble" aria-hidden="true"></i> 33
      </span>
    </div>

    <div class="raul-card mb-5 p-0">
      <pre class="mb-0"><code class="language-markup"><%= (`
        <span class="badge badge-primary">33</span>
        <span class="badge badge-primary">
          <i class="fa fa-dribbble" aria-hidden="true"></i> 33
        </span>
      `) %></code></pre>
    </div>

    <p>
      For bootstrap compatibility, various theme colors are included. However, the design only
      show that the primary is ever used. This needs clarification from design.
    </p>

    <div class="raul-card">
      <span class="badge badge-primary">Primary</span>
      <span class="badge badge-success">Success</span>
      <span class="badge badge-error">Error</span>
      <span class="badge badge-danger">Danger</span>
      <span class="badge badge-warning">Warning</span>
      <span class="badge badge-info">Info</span>
    </div>

    <div class="raul-card mb-5 p-0">
      <pre class="mb-0"><code class="language-markup"><%= (`
        <span class="badge badge-primary">Primary</span>
        <span class="badge badge-success">Success</span>
        <span class="badge badge-error">Error</span>
        <span class="badge badge-danger">Danger</span>
        <span class="badge badge-warning">Warning</span>
        <span class="badge badge-info">Info</span>
      `) %></code></pre>
    </div>

    <h3 class="mb-3">With icons:</h3>

    <div class="raul-card">
      <span class="badge badge-primary">
        <i class="fa fa-bell-o" aria-hidden="true"></i> Primary
      </span>

      <span class="badge badge-success">
        <i class="fa fa-bell-o" aria-hidden="true"></i> Success
      </span>

      <span class="badge badge-error">
        <i class="fa fa-bell-o" aria-hidden="true"></i> Error
      </span>

      <span class="badge badge-danger">
        <i class="fa fa-bell-o" aria-hidden="true"></i> Danger
      </span>

      <span class="badge badge-warning">
        <i class="fa fa-bell-o" aria-hidden="true"></i> Warning
      </span>

      <span class="badge badge-info">
        <i class="fa fa-bell-o" aria-hidden="true"></i> Info
      </span>
    </div>

    <div class="raul-card mb-5 p-0">
      <pre class="mb-0"><code class="language-markup"><%= (`
        <span class="badge badge-primary">
          <i class="fa fa-bell-o" aria-hidden="true"></i> Primary
        </span>

        <span class="badge badge-success">
          <i class="fa fa-bell-o" aria-hidden="true"></i> Success
        </span>

        <span class="badge badge-error">
          <i class="fa fa-bell-o" aria-hidden="true"></i> Error
        </span>

        <span class="badge badge-danger">
          <i class="fa fa-bell-o" aria-hidden="true"></i> Danger
        </span>

        <span class="badge badge-warning">
          <i class="fa fa-bell-o" aria-hidden="true"></i> Warning
        </span>

        <span class="badge badge-info">
          <i class="fa fa-bell-o" aria-hidden="true"></i> Info
        </span>
      `) %></code></pre>
    </div>

    <h2>Backwards compatible RAUL badges</h2>

    <p>
      If you are already using the old RAUL markup for badges, then the original markup is still
      available to use.
    </p>

    <div class="raul-card">
      <div class="raul-badges-container">
        <div class="raul-badge">
          <span class="raul-badge-text">33</span>
        </div>

        <div class="raul-badge">
          <span class="raul-badge-icon">
            <i class="fa fa-dribbble" aria-hidden="true"></i>
          </span>

          <span class="raul-badge-text">33</span>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="raul-card mb-5 p-0">
      <pre class="mb-0"><code class="language-markup"><%= (`
        <div class="raul-badges-container">
          <div class="raul-badge">
            <span class="raul-badge-text">33</span>
          </div>

          <div class="raul-badge">
            <span class="raul-badge-icon">
              <i class="fa fa-dribbble" aria-hidden="true"></i>
            </span>

            <span class="raul-badge-text">33</span>
          </div>
        </div>
      `) %></code></pre>
    </div>
  </div>
</div>

